You can use the OPEN WINDOW statement to create a new window. This statement takes two arguments: the title of the window and the size of it. For example:
```4gl
OPEN WINDOW("New Order");
SIZE(400, 600);
```
This code creates a new window with a title of "New Order" and a size of 400 pixels wide by 600 pixels high. The SIZE clause specifies the dimensions for this new window. When you run this statement in your code, Actian 4GL will display it on top of all other open windows.

You can declare a procedure with a parameter list, which specifies the types and names of its parameters. Then, when you call the procedure, you can provide any number of arguments. For example:
```4gl
PROCEDURE add(x NUMERIC, y STRING)
{
    // Code here
}
```
This code declares a procedure called 'add' that takes two parameters: an integer 'x' and a string 'y'. When you call this procedure, you can provide any number of arguments. The 4GL compiler will automatically determine the values of these parameters based on the data types and names specified in the parameter list.

You can define a function with a return type, which specifies what kind of value it will return when executed. Then, when you call the function, 4GL will evaluate it and return the resulting value to you. For example:
```4gl
