{
    // Code here
}
```
This code defines a function called 'max' that takes an integer parameter 'x'. When you call this function, 4GL will evaluate it and return the maximum value of 'x' to you. You can then use this value in your code, such as comparing it to other values or performing calculations with it.

You can use the FORM statement to define a form. Then, you can add fields to this form using the ADD FIELD clause. For example:
```4gl
FORM("Order")
ADD FIELD(NAME="customer");
ADD FIELD(TYPE=TEXT);
ADD FIELD(VALUE="John Doe");
DISPLAY(TITLE:"Order Form");
```
This code creates an "Order" form and adds three fields to it. The first field is called 'customer' and its data type is set to TEXT. Its initial value is set to 'John Doe'. Then the form is displayed with the title "Order Form". You can now use this form in your code, such as performing actions with its fields or setting their values.

You can open a new dialog box with the OPEN DIALOG statement. Then, you can set its title and size using the TITLE and SIZE clauses. For example:
```4gl
